<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="191" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,972,2007]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1152,1178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along part of its extension. Anterolateral margin dorsally weakly punctured. Cicatrices of pronotum with punctures brown and concolorous delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[288,391,1224,1250]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 18C</figureCitation>
). Posterior part of pronotum with a somewhat faded black stripe (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1236,1224,1250]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 18C</figureCitation>
). Anterior margin of scutellum greenish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[498,603,1260,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 18C</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with dark lines (
<figureCitation box="[990,1096,1260,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1297,1424,1260,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with dorsal rim rugose and shallowly excavated (
<figureCitation box="[824,913,1296,1322]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface with two swollen conspicuous lateral areas adjacent to dorsal rim (
<figureCitation box="[561,653,1332,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup reniform, medially concave, brown and adjacent to dorsal rim; not visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[756,879,1368,1394]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2A–C</figureCitation>
). Parameres elongated, golf club shaped, laterally curved; anterior lobe very short and rounded; posterior lobe developed and subtriangular; inner face of the stalk with a high carina ending at the apex of posterior lobe (
<figureCitation box="[702,822,1440,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger strongly compressed laterally with dorsolateral tufts of long setae separated by a median bridge without setae; posterior face barrel-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1216,1338,1476,1502]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2B–D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with median excavation “V” shaped, margin slightly sloping ventrally; expansions not developed, rounded, almost level with posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[772,896,1548,1574]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2B–D</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="191" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,972,2007]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1584,1610]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Comments.</emphasis>
This species has the posterior stripe of pronotum slightly faded (
<figureCitation box="[1076,1180,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 18C</figureCitation>
), unlike the rest of the species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1803" box="[317,443,1620,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridens">
<emphasis box="[317,443,1620,1646]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">quadridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. This species belongs to the group of species with paramere with posterior lobe well-developed and anterior lobe barely developed, like a golf club (
<figureCitation box="[933,1057,1656,1682]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2B–C</figureCitation>
). This group gathers nine species that can be separated by the shape of the paramere and superior process of genital cup. The species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1290,1436,1692,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bitumidus">
<emphasis box="[1290,1436,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">H. bitumidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the group with superior process of the genital cup oblong and curved (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1163,1728,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2B–C</figureCitation>
) together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1330,1436,1728,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[1330,1436,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">H. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,298,1764,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777088" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777088/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 14B–C</figureCitation>
). Both species have posterior lobe of the paramere triangular and anterior lobe rounded and barely developed (
<figureCitation box="[281,380,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Figs. 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[391,441,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777088" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777088/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">14B</figureCitation>
). But these species can be separated by the pair of swollen areas close to dorsal rim (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
), posterior face of the proctiger barrel-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[716,828,1836,1862]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2B,D</figureCitation>
) and expansions of ventral rim barely developed (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777064" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777064/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[229,372,1872,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bitumidus">
<emphasis box="[229,372,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">H. bitumidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(without pair of swollen areas, posterior face pentagonal and expansions of ventral rim strongly developed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[302,409,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[302,409,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">H. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1125,1944,1971]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,972,2007]" box="[199,1125,1944,1971]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1944,1970]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the tumid lateral areas on dorsal rim of the pygophore.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
